WEBVTT

00:09.426 --> 00:11.927
We are approaching
Starbase 1 79, sir.

00:12.137 --> 00:13.429
Half impulse, Mr. Crusher.

00:13.638 --> 00:15.347
Going to half impulse.

00:15.515 --> 00:16.640
Captain, this is the Bridge.

00:16.850 --> 00:19.018
We've arrived at Starbase 1 79.

00:19.185 --> 00:20.936
PlCARD [OVER lNTERCOM]:
Acknowledged, Number One.

00:21.104 --> 00:26.984
Establish position 090, mark 345
at 27,000 kilometers.

00:27.318 --> 00:28.610
Hailing frequencies.

00:29.362 --> 00:32.740
- Open.
- Starbase 1 79, this is the Enterprise.

00:32.949 --> 00:35.367
WOMAN [OVER lNTERCOM]:
Enterprise, this is Starbase 179.

00:35.535 --> 00:37.703
We are ready for transfer
on your mark.

00:37.871 --> 00:41.707
Thank you. Data, you have the Bridge.
Ensign Crusher, you're with me.

00:56.890 --> 00:59.933
Starbase 1 79, we are ready
to commence transfer.

01:00.143 --> 01:03.479
WOMAN: Acknowledged, Enterprise.
Begin transfer.

01:11.112 --> 01:12.654
Welcome aboard the Enterprise.

01:12.864 --> 01:15.074
l'm Commander William Riker,
your first officer.

01:15.283 --> 01:17.826
Those of you who are here
as replacements can step outside

01:18.036 --> 01:19.286
and follow Lieutenant Lewis.

01:19.496 --> 01:22.039
He will assign you
to your crew quarters.

01:22.916 --> 01:24.625
Ensign, you're here
on the exchange program,

01:24.834 --> 01:26.335
if you would just follow Mr. Crusher.

01:26.544 --> 01:27.961
Mordock, what are you doing here?

01:28.129 --> 01:30.214
You couldn't have graduated
from the Academy already.

01:31.841 --> 01:34.301
l am not Mordock. l am Mendon.

01:34.469 --> 01:37.221
Ensign Mendon
from the planet Benzar.

01:37.388 --> 01:39.681
Sorry. Uh, it's a friend of mine.

01:39.849 --> 01:40.891
You look just like him.

01:41.059 --> 01:45.062
We are from the same geostructure.
Naturally we look alike.

01:45.688 --> 01:47.189
How do you tell each other apart?

01:49.776 --> 01:51.693
We just do.

01:53.154 --> 01:55.114
lt's nice to have you here, ensign.

01:55.824 --> 01:59.034
There will be a briefing and
indoctrination session in 1 5 minutes.

01:59.953 --> 02:03.622
l want to tell you how happy l am
to be assigned to the Enterprise.

02:03.832 --> 02:06.166
lt wasn't just luck. l requested it.

02:06.376 --> 02:09.419
l know l can be of great help
to the ship.

02:09.963 --> 02:12.631
Yes, of course.
lf you'll just follow Mr. Crusher.

02:12.841 --> 02:14.591
Yes, sir.

02:18.096 --> 02:19.304
[CHUCKLES]

02:19.472 --> 02:20.681
PlCARD [OVER lNTERCOM]:
Commander Riker,

02:20.849 --> 02:23.851
- report to the phaser range, please.
- On my way.

02:26.938 --> 02:27.980
[BEEPlNG]

02:33.403 --> 02:35.154
l was wondering
if you had any feelings

02:35.321 --> 02:39.700
about the officer-exchange program
initiated by Starfleet Command.

02:39.909 --> 02:41.285
Just positive ones, sir.

02:41.494 --> 02:45.497
Actually, l just welcomed
Ensign Mendon onboard.

02:45.707 --> 02:47.541
He certainly seems eager to please.

02:47.750 --> 02:49.877
Well, that's a Benzite trait.

02:53.965 --> 02:56.633
lt's been suggested
that an officer from the Enterprise

02:56.801 --> 02:59.136
might participate in the program.

03:00.180 --> 03:02.514
That's probably a good idea.

03:03.308 --> 03:06.977
Well, there is a Klingon vessel
in the area.

03:10.648 --> 03:12.482
l don't recall hearing
of a Federation officer

03:12.650 --> 03:14.651
ever serving on a Klingon vessel.

03:14.861 --> 03:17.154
No, no, neither have l.

03:17.697 --> 03:19.364
lt might prove to be beneficial.

03:19.574 --> 03:22.326
Well, having Worf onboard
certainly has been.

03:22.535 --> 03:24.161
Yes, sir.

03:25.413 --> 03:27.414
Who did you intend to send, sir?

03:28.082 --> 03:29.875
l thought of asking for a volunteer.

03:30.084 --> 03:31.210
l might be interested, sir.

03:31.377 --> 03:34.588
Damn. Sorry, Number One.
What was that?

03:34.797 --> 03:37.257
l said l wouldn't mind
the assignment, sir.

03:38.885 --> 03:40.928
Any particular reason?

03:41.387 --> 03:43.972
Because nobody's ever done it before.

03:45.934 --> 03:48.268
Well, l'll inform starbase
of your acceptance.

03:48.436 --> 03:51.939
They'll contact the Klingon vessel,
make the arrangements.

03:52.106 --> 03:53.190
[BEEPlNG]

04:13.670 --> 04:17.923
PlCARD:
Space, the final frontier.

04:18.508 --> 04:22.427
These are the voyages
ofthe starship Enterprise.

04:22.637 --> 04:27.808
lts continuing mission:
to explore strange new worlds,

04:28.476 --> 04:32.562
to seek out new life
and new civilizations,

04:33.022 --> 04:37.359
to boldly go where no one
has gone before.

05:33.416 --> 05:36.877
PlCARD:
Captain's log, stardate 42506.5.

05:37.086 --> 05:39.880
We have departed
from Starbase 179

05:40.089 --> 05:43.592
and are headed for a rendezvous
with the Klingon vessel, Pagh.

05:43.801 --> 05:45.010
l have informed the staff

05:45.219 --> 05:47.220
of Commander Riker's
temporary assignment.

05:47.805 --> 05:50.390
l have studied and know everything
about my heritage.

05:50.600 --> 05:52.809
Then you're just the person l need
to clear something up.

05:53.019 --> 05:55.562
lt's my understanding
that one of the duties of the first officer

05:55.772 --> 05:57.773
of the Klingon vessel
is to assassinate his captain?

05:57.982 --> 05:59.066
Yes, sir.

05:59.233 --> 06:01.860
- Wouldn't that bring about chaos?
- Of course not.

06:02.070 --> 06:05.489
See, when and if the captain
becomes weak or unable to perform,

06:05.698 --> 06:08.492
it is expected
that his honorable retirement

06:08.659 --> 06:10.202
should be assisted by his first.

06:10.411 --> 06:14.331
Your second officer will assassinate
you for the same reasons.

06:14.540 --> 06:17.000
That method of attrition
must take a little getting used to.

06:17.210 --> 06:21.088
The Klingon system has operated
successfully for centuries.

06:21.422 --> 06:23.173
lt is different.

06:23.966 --> 06:26.426
Many things will be different.

06:30.223 --> 06:31.473
[SlGHS]

06:54.288 --> 06:56.873
[WHlRRlNG AND BEEPlNG]

06:57.250 --> 06:58.750
Can l help you, sir?

06:58.960 --> 07:00.043
That's a wonderful method

07:00.211 --> 07:03.839
of maintaining a constant control factor
over defensive shields,

07:04.048 --> 07:07.551
but l'm sure there's a way
to improve response time.

07:09.887 --> 07:12.222
Sorry. Didn't mean to interrupt you.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.224
Just thought l could be
of some help.

07:15.435 --> 07:19.020
However, l am correct in what l said.

07:27.280 --> 07:28.572
[HELM CONSOLE BEEPlNG]

07:32.994 --> 07:34.870
That is superb designing.

07:35.037 --> 07:37.164
Absolutely first rate.

07:37.373 --> 07:40.167
Yes, it is.
Would you care to be more specific?

07:40.376 --> 07:44.212
The input sampling.
lt's simple, yet efficient enough.

07:44.422 --> 07:46.798
Of course, a minor change
of the helm readout

07:47.008 --> 07:49.843
would be much more helpful
in emergency situations.

07:50.052 --> 07:51.970
We've never had any problems
with it.

07:52.180 --> 07:53.430
Have you seen it work?

07:53.639 --> 07:58.435
Not in a practical exercise,
but in theory, my theory,

07:58.644 --> 08:01.104
it would be more
than a marginal improvement.

08:01.314 --> 08:03.607
l'll have to mention this
to the captain.

08:03.816 --> 08:07.486
He is open to some astute
observations, isn't he?

08:08.029 --> 08:11.406
l've never known the captain
not to listen to one of his officers.

08:11.616 --> 08:12.699
MENDON:
Outstanding.

08:12.909 --> 08:15.994
Soon we'll get things
running perfectly.

08:21.959 --> 08:24.419
[CHATTERlNG]

08:33.221 --> 08:35.138
What is that?

08:35.848 --> 08:37.224
lt's a Klingon delicacy.

08:37.433 --> 08:39.142
Pipius claw.

08:39.352 --> 08:40.810
This is heart of targ.

08:41.020 --> 08:43.063
This, of course, is gagh.

08:43.606 --> 08:45.106
Gagh?

08:45.316 --> 08:46.691
Serpent worms.
Would you like some?

08:46.901 --> 08:48.568
PULASKl:
No, thanks. Ha.

08:48.778 --> 08:51.905
l've never heard of a Klingon starving
to death on his own vessel,

08:52.114 --> 08:53.990
- but you might.
- Not if l weaken first.

08:54.158 --> 08:56.660
l know all about that.
Their beliefs are rather brutal,

08:56.827 --> 09:00.580
but usually, what kills us kills them.

09:01.666 --> 09:04.292
That's certainly good to know.
Would you like something to drink?

09:04.502 --> 09:08.129
Heh. l'm abstaining in honor
of your last hour onboard.

09:08.339 --> 09:11.216
Your sacrifice will not go unnoticed.

09:13.844 --> 09:14.886
PULASKl:
Ugh...

09:15.054 --> 09:16.596
- Well...
RlKER: Oh.

09:16.806 --> 09:19.474
l'm familiar with the practice
of a feast before the transfer.

09:19.684 --> 09:21.226
l've done it dozens of times.

09:21.811 --> 09:24.896
However, l usually made
more palatable choices.

09:25.439 --> 09:28.567
Well, these are the more
palatable choices.

09:28.734 --> 09:30.694
Ah. Thank you.

09:32.488 --> 09:34.948
Mm. Uh--

09:37.076 --> 09:38.743
We know so little about them.

09:38.953 --> 09:42.122
There really is so much to learn.

09:42.290 --> 09:44.833
This is a great opportunity.

09:45.209 --> 09:47.002
l envy you, Mr. Riker.

09:48.170 --> 09:49.546
Oh.

09:49.839 --> 09:51.298
PULASKl:
Ah.

09:55.011 --> 09:57.721
- Ah.
- Yeah, thank you.

09:59.056 --> 10:00.432
Oh...

10:03.394 --> 10:05.562
[CRUNCHlNG]

10:06.147 --> 10:07.188
Mm.

10:14.322 --> 10:16.072
Commander.

10:18.367 --> 10:19.784
An emergency transponder?

10:19.994 --> 10:22.495
Slightly altered to transmit
an omnidirectional signal

10:22.705 --> 10:24.205
and an emergency call.

10:24.415 --> 10:25.624
You suspect trouble?

10:25.833 --> 10:27.208
Simply a security precaution.

10:27.418 --> 10:30.420
l want to insure your return
to this ship.

10:30.630 --> 10:33.006
Sentiment, Lieutenant Worf?

10:33.215 --> 10:35.258
Efficiency, commander.

10:35.468 --> 10:38.219
l understand. Thank you.

10:42.099 --> 10:43.558
[BEEPlNG]

10:43.726 --> 10:46.478
We have a Klingon vessel
approaching.

10:46.687 --> 10:49.439
- Hailing frequencies.
- Open.

10:49.774 --> 10:51.941
They are returning our hail
in proper language.

10:52.151 --> 10:54.194
lt is the Pagh.

10:54.445 --> 10:56.237
On viewscreen.

10:59.575 --> 11:02.702
l am Captain Picard
of the USS Enterprise.

11:03.245 --> 11:06.790
This is Captain Kargan
of the Klingon vessel, the Pagh.

11:07.166 --> 11:10.126
Beam your first officer onboard
immediately.

11:10.544 --> 11:12.420
We are preparing to do so.

11:12.630 --> 11:16.049
And, captain,
you're getting a fine officer.

11:16.217 --> 11:20.220
Thank you for your opinion,
but l will judge that for myself.

11:20.429 --> 11:22.555
Screen off.

11:27.812 --> 11:29.979
MENDON:
Not very hospitable, are they?

11:30.189 --> 11:31.731
That is not your concern.

11:31.941 --> 11:34.567
Observe your station,
Ensign Mendon.

11:36.278 --> 11:38.154
Didn't mean to offend you.

11:38.364 --> 11:39.739
You didn't.

11:39.907 --> 11:41.074
Yet.

11:47.915 --> 11:50.709
[BEEPlNG]

12:19.321 --> 12:21.823
Transporter, prepare to beam
Commander Riker aboard the Pagh.

12:22.032 --> 12:23.908
O'BRlEN [OVER lNTERCOM]:
Acknowledged, captain.

12:24.577 --> 12:28.121
- Mr. Data, you have the Bridge.
DATA: Aye, sir.

12:32.543 --> 12:34.419
[BEEPlNG]

12:39.717 --> 12:42.343
O'BRlEN: Good luck, commander.
RlKER: Thanks, O'Brien.

12:42.553 --> 12:44.637
- l wouldn't want to go.
- Why?

12:44.805 --> 12:48.349
- Heh. You're not afraid, are you?
- No, l'm not.

12:48.893 --> 12:49.976
l would be.

12:50.144 --> 12:51.561
Uh, ready, sir.

12:52.897 --> 12:54.230
Thanks.

12:54.440 --> 12:55.815
Energize.

13:14.460 --> 13:17.462
PlCARD: Resume course, Mr. Crusher.
WESLEY: Aye, sir.

13:18.088 --> 13:20.465
Take over, Commander Data.
l'll be in observation.

13:20.674 --> 13:22.342
Thank you, sir.

13:23.344 --> 13:24.803
MENDON:
Sir.

13:25.596 --> 13:27.138
l am Ensign Mendon.

13:27.348 --> 13:29.098
l just wanted to tell you
how pleased l am

13:29.266 --> 13:31.643
to be aboard the Enterprise.

13:31.977 --> 13:33.019
Yes, of course.

13:33.187 --> 13:35.438
Uh, good to have you aboard.

13:35.648 --> 13:40.026
lf you have a few minutes,
l've noted a few procedural changes

13:40.194 --> 13:42.612
which might speed up operations
on the Bridge.

13:42.822 --> 13:44.614
l pick things up very fast.

13:45.157 --> 13:47.575
Yes, of course you do.
You have an excellent record, ensign.

13:47.785 --> 13:51.371
However, here on the Enterprise,
we use the chain of command.

13:51.580 --> 13:54.541
You will report your observations
to Lieutenant Worf.

13:54.750 --> 13:57.794
l beg your pardon, captain.
l just wanted to impress upon you--

13:58.003 --> 13:59.754
No need to apologize, ensign.

13:59.964 --> 14:02.715
We should have explained it better
to you at your indoctrination.

14:04.093 --> 14:07.053
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

14:10.474 --> 14:12.350
Ensign Mendon...

14:15.855 --> 14:18.314
...you may impress me.

14:28.158 --> 14:29.993
[SPEAKlNG lNDlSTlNCTLY]

14:39.169 --> 14:42.297
- ls something wrong?
- No.

14:42.631 --> 14:48.720
lt's just l've never seen anyone
of your species before.

14:48.888 --> 14:50.513
l'm just your average
everyday human being

14:50.681 --> 14:52.974
who happens to be a commander.

14:53.809 --> 14:55.101
Now, what were your orders?

14:55.269 --> 14:57.937
To escort you to the captain.

15:00.649 --> 15:01.858
Proceed.

15:02.067 --> 15:04.444
Yes, commander.

15:31.472 --> 15:34.182
RlKER: Commander William Riker
of the starship Enterprise.

15:34.391 --> 15:36.768
That is incorrect.

15:37.770 --> 15:39.145
RlKER:
l don't understand.

15:39.355 --> 15:42.148
You are Commander William Riker,

15:42.358 --> 15:46.653
first officer of the Klingon cruiser,
the Pagh.

15:46.862 --> 15:50.698
Or do you intend
to disobey Federation orders?

15:51.325 --> 15:53.242
l have no such intentions, sir.

15:53.452 --> 15:57.580
Exactly where are your loyalties,
commander?

15:58.707 --> 16:01.000
l'm afraid l still don't understand, sir.

16:01.210 --> 16:04.253
This ship is equipped
with our best weapons

16:04.421 --> 16:06.255
and our finest warriors.

16:06.465 --> 16:08.383
Although we are
on a peaceful mission,

16:08.592 --> 16:10.760
we are ready to go into battle
instantly.

16:10.928 --> 16:14.305
l know l can count on every
Klingon warrior in this crew

16:14.515 --> 16:16.891
to serve and die in that battle.

16:17.101 --> 16:22.021
So l ask you again, Commander Riker,
where are your loyalties?

16:24.692 --> 16:28.945
l've been assigned to serve this ship
and to obey your orders.

16:29.154 --> 16:31.239
And l will do exactly that.

16:31.448 --> 16:33.783
Will you take an oath to that effect?

16:33.993 --> 16:35.535
l just did.

16:36.787 --> 16:39.122
[lN KLlNGON]

16:46.672 --> 16:48.464
[lN ENGLlSH]
This is your second officer,

16:48.632 --> 16:50.758
Lieutenant Klag.

16:53.429 --> 16:55.888
Was there something you wanted
to say to me, lieutenant?

16:59.893 --> 17:01.686
Yes, sir.

17:03.856 --> 17:07.400
l do not believe you.

17:07.568 --> 17:09.986
Then l take it you challenge
my authority over you.

17:10.904 --> 17:12.989
Correct.

17:14.616 --> 17:17.326
And your position on this, captain?

17:17.494 --> 17:22.790
l would say
it is your first command decision.

17:27.463 --> 17:28.880
[SNARLS]

17:32.176 --> 17:33.384
[GRUNTlNG]

17:57.367 --> 18:01.704
My oath is between Captain Kargan
and myself.

18:02.247 --> 18:06.292
Your only concern
is with how you obey my orders.

18:06.877 --> 18:09.962
Or do you prefer the rank of prisoner
to that of lieutenant?

18:10.798 --> 18:13.174
l will take your orders.

18:15.219 --> 18:19.263
And you, Commander Riker,
obey my orders.

18:19.473 --> 18:21.808
Of course, Captain Kargan.

18:23.936 --> 18:24.977
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

18:32.945 --> 18:33.986
[BEEPlNG]

18:34.154 --> 18:37.532
Sir, automatic scan
has registered an unknown substance

18:37.741 --> 18:40.284
on the aft quarter of the exterior skin
of the dorsal section.

18:40.494 --> 18:43.454
- Target that location and define.
WORF: Aye, sir.

18:44.706 --> 18:46.207
l've located it, sir.

18:46.416 --> 18:48.459
The dorsal
of the Engineering section.

18:48.669 --> 18:50.461
Viewscreen on.

18:52.256 --> 18:54.215
Focus on area.

18:54.383 --> 18:57.218
Magnification factor ten.

18:58.679 --> 19:00.555
lncrease magnification to 50.

19:01.932 --> 19:03.683
PlCARD:
Analyze.

19:03.892 --> 19:06.978
The substance appears to be
a rare form of subatomic bacteria,

19:07.187 --> 19:10.898
capable of doubling itself in size
every 1 5 minutes.

19:11.108 --> 19:13.693
lt seems to be reacting
with two of the compounds present

19:13.902 --> 19:15.027
in the Enterprise structure.

19:15.237 --> 19:18.030
- Origin.
- Captain, l noticed it

19:18.240 --> 19:20.491
when l did an intensive scan
of the Pagh.

19:21.493 --> 19:23.411
The Klingon ship.

19:23.871 --> 19:25.329
And whom did you inform?

19:25.539 --> 19:29.041
Well, no one. l have not yet completed
my full analysis.

19:29.251 --> 19:32.545
You are supposed to report
whatever is out of the ordinary.

19:33.463 --> 19:35.882
And l think that falls
into this category.

19:36.091 --> 19:39.302
But, sir, as l said, l have not yet
completed my full analysis.

19:39.511 --> 19:42.805
lt would be improper to report it
until then.

19:42.973 --> 19:45.600
How did you come to that decision?

19:46.268 --> 19:48.311
lt is a Benzite regulation.

19:48.520 --> 19:50.688
No officer on the deck
of one of our ships

19:50.898 --> 19:52.315
would report an occurrence like this

19:52.524 --> 19:55.276
until he had a full analysis
and a resolution.

19:56.111 --> 19:58.946
l have simply followed
proper procedures.

20:05.662 --> 20:08.331
lt is our procedure, ensign,

20:08.540 --> 20:13.169
to notify command
of any possible danger to the ship.

20:13.378 --> 20:14.795
The decision is not yours.

20:15.005 --> 20:16.505
Do you understand?

20:16.673 --> 20:17.882
Yes, sir.

20:18.926 --> 20:21.052
Now, you will continue
with your analysis

20:21.261 --> 20:22.303
and determine the danger

20:22.512 --> 20:25.139
not only to our ship
but to the Klingon vessel also.

20:25.682 --> 20:29.852
Yes, captain.
That will take a couple of hours.

20:30.062 --> 20:31.854
Use whatever resources
are necessary.

20:32.064 --> 20:34.899
lt appears we may have encountered
a new life-form.

20:35.108 --> 20:37.526
l want to know everything about it
as quickly as possible.

20:37.736 --> 20:40.821
- Commander Data, supervise.
- Aye, sir.

20:48.163 --> 20:51.874
And then l will instruct you
in Enterprise etiquette.

20:58.298 --> 21:00.424
RlKER:
First officer's personal log.

21:00.634 --> 21:02.718
I have been aboard the Pagh
a short time,

21:02.886 --> 21:04.887
but long enough to be impressed
with the abilities

21:05.055 --> 21:07.223
and single-mindedness
of the Klingons.

21:07.391 --> 21:09.392
[MUNCHlNG
AND SLURPlNG LOUDLY]

21:14.231 --> 21:15.398
KLlNGON 1 :
Mm.

21:15.565 --> 21:17.608
[CHATTERlNG lN KLlNGON]

21:26.702 --> 21:28.202
[KLlNGON 2 LAUGHS]

21:35.460 --> 21:38.254
Commander,
you're not eating very much.

21:38.964 --> 21:40.506
l'm not that hungry.

21:40.716 --> 21:44.093
- ls the food all right, commander?
- lt's delicious.

21:44.303 --> 21:47.471
The Pipius claw was excellent.
l also enjoyed this Bregit lung.

21:47.889 --> 21:50.224
And the Rokeg blood pie?

21:50.767 --> 21:52.435
Delicious.

21:52.978 --> 21:57.648
Good. Then you'll also enjoy this.

21:59.693 --> 22:01.694
lsn't that gagh?

22:01.903 --> 22:05.406
Very good. You did some research
on our nutritional choices.

22:05.615 --> 22:06.824
Yes, but...

22:10.078 --> 22:12.121
...uh, it's still moving.

22:12.331 --> 22:15.249
Gagh is always best
when served live.

22:20.213 --> 22:21.255
[SlGHS]

22:21.423 --> 22:23.758
Would you like something easier?

22:24.301 --> 22:25.676
Easier?

22:27.679 --> 22:31.724
Yes.
lf Klingon food is too strong for you,

22:31.933 --> 22:35.936
perhaps we could get one
of the females to breast-feed you.

22:36.104 --> 22:38.022
[KLlNGONS LAUGHlNG]

22:49.493 --> 22:51.744
You're not worried
about my weakening, are you?

22:51.912 --> 22:53.162
[LAUGHS]

22:53.330 --> 22:55.164
Look around you.

22:55.374 --> 22:58.000
There are no old warriors.

22:58.210 --> 23:00.878
No, sir.
l'm sure they all died with honor.

23:01.671 --> 23:03.714
Exactly.

23:04.883 --> 23:08.260
You may live long enough
to learn about us.

23:09.638 --> 23:12.473
VEKMA:
Mm, he is not very attractive,

23:13.016 --> 23:14.433
but l will have him.

23:14.601 --> 23:15.768
[KLlNGONS MURMURlNG]

23:15.936 --> 23:17.812
KLlNGON 3:
They are inquisitive.

23:18.021 --> 23:20.314
They would like to know
how you would endure.

23:20.690 --> 23:21.899
Endure what?

23:22.275 --> 23:23.818
Them.

23:25.028 --> 23:26.487
[KLlNGONS LAUGHlNG]

23:28.824 --> 23:31.242
[KLlNGONS MURMURlNG
AND CHATTERlNG]

23:32.494 --> 23:34.453
One or both?

23:34.621 --> 23:37.081
[KLlNGONS CHATTERlNG
AND LAUGHlNG]

23:45.799 --> 23:49.260
l may be back for you.

23:49.428 --> 23:52.555
[KLlNGONS LAUGHlNG]

23:55.892 --> 23:57.560
ls she serious?

23:57.727 --> 23:59.478
KLAG:
Yes.

24:02.524 --> 24:05.443
[CHATTERlNG lN KLlNGON]

24:07.112 --> 24:13.117
Commander, would you say
you're a typical Federation officer?

24:13.285 --> 24:15.286
l suppose so. Why?

24:15.495 --> 24:17.580
Well, it's just you're not
what l expected.

24:17.789 --> 24:18.956
ln what way?

24:19.166 --> 24:21.041
You have a sense of humor.

24:21.501 --> 24:23.252
l was thinking the same thing
about you.

24:23.462 --> 24:27.256
ln all my dealings with Klingons,
including our Lieutenant Worf,

24:27.466 --> 24:31.010
the thought never occurred to me
of Klingons laughing.

24:31.219 --> 24:34.221
There is much about us
you do not know.

24:34.764 --> 24:36.348
That's why l'm here.

24:36.558 --> 24:38.058
You should ask.

24:38.268 --> 24:42.605
l may. After this tour,
l may have some worthy questions.

24:42.814 --> 24:44.773
Questions about what?

24:44.983 --> 24:46.817
About our future?

24:47.027 --> 24:49.111
Our future is honor.

24:49.696 --> 24:52.823
- Our present is serving this ship.
KLlNGON 4: Yes.

24:52.991 --> 24:56.243
Like you,
l have a mother and a father.

24:56.453 --> 24:59.455
They look like me. l look like them.

24:59.789 --> 25:02.082
- Are they still alive?
- My mother lives.

25:02.292 --> 25:05.628
And my father was killed
in battle at Tranome Sar.

25:08.340 --> 25:10.591
And your father?

25:11.801 --> 25:13.928
My father...?

25:23.605 --> 25:30.069
My father was captured in battle
by Romulans and not allowed to die.

25:31.571 --> 25:34.156
He eventually escaped.

25:34.366 --> 25:36.242
RlKER:
Where is he now?

25:37.118 --> 25:39.662
He is on our planet.

25:41.831 --> 25:43.499
He waits.

25:46.211 --> 25:49.004
He waits for his death.

25:49.548 --> 25:53.300
He will eventually fade
of a natural illness and die,

25:53.468 --> 25:55.719
weakened and useless.

25:55.929 --> 25:57.930
Honorless.

25:58.348 --> 26:00.849
l will not see him.

26:01.393 --> 26:03.143
He's your father.

26:03.311 --> 26:08.482
The Klingon is his work,
not his family.

26:08.775 --> 26:12.236
That is the way of things.

26:16.700 --> 26:18.492
He's your father.

26:18.660 --> 26:23.455
Klingons do not express feeling
the way you do.

26:23.665 --> 26:25.249
Perhaps you should.

26:26.501 --> 26:29.753
We would not know how.

26:35.260 --> 26:40.055
Yesterday l did not know
how to eat gagh.

26:51.359 --> 26:53.819
[BEEPlNG AND WHlRRlNG]

26:56.031 --> 26:59.283
lt is confirmed that the organisms
feed on some of the compounds

26:59.492 --> 27:01.076
that make up the hull
of the Enterprise.

27:01.286 --> 27:03.037
And the Klingon ship, the Pagh?

27:03.455 --> 27:05.205
They are more susceptible.

27:05.415 --> 27:07.750
Their hull contains more
of the compounds.

27:09.085 --> 27:10.127
Projection.

27:12.505 --> 27:13.964
According to the rate
of reproduction,

27:14.174 --> 27:17.760
there should be a 12-centimeter
opening in the Klingon hull at this time.

27:17.969 --> 27:20.554
Signal them at once. They could be
unaware of their danger.

27:20.764 --> 27:23.432
- They may need our help.
- Aye, sir.

27:23.642 --> 27:25.726
- Change course to intercept.
WESLEY: Aye, sir.

27:25.935 --> 27:27.811
lt will take some time
to locate them, sir.

27:28.021 --> 27:30.814
They are on undesignated maneuvers
in the Pheben system.

27:31.024 --> 27:32.524
Find them.

27:48.041 --> 27:51.085
Tell me, Commander Riker,
what do you make of this?

27:51.252 --> 27:53.712
[BEEPlNG]

27:53.880 --> 27:55.089
RlKER:
l felt no collision.

27:55.298 --> 27:58.008
- Were we hit by a small meteor?
- No. No collision.

27:58.218 --> 28:00.969
- Corrosion then?
- No, not corrosion.

28:01.179 --> 28:02.262
Science station, analyze.

28:02.472 --> 28:04.682
We already have and, fortunately,
the cavity opened

28:04.849 --> 28:08.018
onto a section that could withstand
the change in pressure.

28:08.228 --> 28:09.353
Then what is it?

28:09.562 --> 28:10.604
KLAG:
A space organism,

28:10.772 --> 28:12.981
- eating away at our hull.
- What are you talking about?

28:13.149 --> 28:15.651
What is it? l mean,
you must have some way to repair it.

28:16.027 --> 28:17.236
l'm afraid not.

28:17.445 --> 28:19.863
Our estimate
is that in less than eight hours,

28:20.073 --> 28:24.326
we will have lost too much
of our shell to remain intact.

28:24.536 --> 28:27.913
The only vessel we've had contact with
recently is the Enterprise.

28:28.123 --> 28:31.041
There was no direct contact
with the Enterprise.

28:31.459 --> 28:34.753
Tactics officer,
report to Commander Riker.

28:34.963 --> 28:38.882
The Enterprise did conduct
an extensive scan of this vessel.

28:39.092 --> 28:40.676
That's normal procedure.

28:41.177 --> 28:44.888
What type of beam did the Enterprise
use to cause this damage to our hull?

28:45.098 --> 28:47.558
None. Why would they do that?
We're allies.

28:47.767 --> 28:48.809
But my logs indicate

28:48.977 --> 28:52.020
that the Enterprise
directed an intense scanning beam

28:52.188 --> 28:54.189
at this specific area

28:54.399 --> 28:56.692
for a duration of two minutes.

28:57.235 --> 28:58.944
Explain that.

29:03.408 --> 29:05.117
l can't.

29:05.326 --> 29:06.744
lt could be a weapon.

29:08.121 --> 29:09.621
lt's no weapon.

29:09.831 --> 29:12.541
The Enterprise has no reason
to do that, especially with me onboard.

29:12.751 --> 29:14.293
lt makes no sense. Why?

29:14.502 --> 29:16.712
Why is no longer important.

29:16.921 --> 29:19.840
What is important
is our response to this attack.

29:20.049 --> 29:21.508
Engage cloaking device.

29:21.718 --> 29:23.886
Change course
to intercept the Enterprise.

29:24.095 --> 29:25.637
What do you intend to do, captain?

29:25.847 --> 29:28.766
lntend? There's only one response.

29:28.975 --> 29:32.936
l intend to attack the Enterprise
and destroy it.

29:57.045 --> 29:58.587
You're making some progress.

29:59.506 --> 30:02.841
You've eliminated
half the possibilities already.

30:03.301 --> 30:04.426
Thank you.

30:04.636 --> 30:07.721
But l seem to have become efficient
a little later than was needed.

30:07.931 --> 30:10.682
lt was my responsibility
to learn and adapt

30:10.850 --> 30:13.393
to the Enterprise's regulations.

30:13.853 --> 30:16.063
And l didn't do that.

30:16.856 --> 30:18.774
Not really.

30:19.067 --> 30:20.234
You just made an error.

30:22.570 --> 30:25.072
Captain Picard may not like them,

30:25.281 --> 30:27.366
but he knows they turn up
from time to time.

30:27.575 --> 30:29.159
l failed.

30:29.369 --> 30:33.205
l had an opportunity to show
the captain my superior capabilities,

30:33.414 --> 30:34.998
and l failed.

30:35.875 --> 30:38.377
l can never recover from that.

30:39.504 --> 30:42.256
Mendon, it was a mistake.

30:42.465 --> 30:44.466
You didn't put the organism
on the hull.

30:44.676 --> 30:45.926
You discovered it.

30:46.135 --> 30:50.848
You were trying to analyze it
and messed up on protocol a little.

31:03.653 --> 31:05.737
l realize you are trying
to be nice to me,

31:05.905 --> 31:07.990
and l appreciate it.

31:08.199 --> 31:10.576
What l don't understand is why.

31:11.411 --> 31:12.661
Why not?

31:12.871 --> 31:14.621
l thought you could use a friend.

31:15.707 --> 31:17.374
Thank you.

31:17.625 --> 31:21.420
l only hope l can learn your ways
before l mess up again.

31:22.046 --> 31:25.465
l imagine my methods
must seem foolish to you.

31:25.675 --> 31:28.343
They're different.

31:28.553 --> 31:31.138
But that's what this exchange program
is all about.

31:31.347 --> 31:32.806
You learn the way we do things

31:33.016 --> 31:35.100
and take that information
back to your command.

31:35.518 --> 31:38.103
lt's up to them to decide
which is better.

31:39.105 --> 31:41.440
You're right. l'll do it your way.

31:41.649 --> 31:44.067
l'll work even harder
than l did before.

31:44.277 --> 31:46.278
And l'll succeed brilliantly.

31:50.783 --> 31:52.784
[BEEPlNG]

31:54.245 --> 31:56.163
What is the status?

31:56.331 --> 31:57.581
Unchanged.

31:57.790 --> 31:59.917
The rate of increase continues.

32:00.293 --> 32:04.713
Commander Riker, check
the organism growth with Engineering.

32:10.011 --> 32:13.096
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

32:13.264 --> 32:16.308
Keep him under scrutiny.

32:17.644 --> 32:19.227
Captain.

32:19.979 --> 32:23.607
l'm not convinced Riker knew
of any plot against us.

32:23.816 --> 32:28.028
lf he did,
why would he have come onboard?

32:28.571 --> 32:30.447
Because he was ordered to.

32:30.657 --> 32:31.865
To die?

32:32.075 --> 32:36.703
lt is the expectation of any officer
to be ordered to die at any time.

32:36.913 --> 32:38.580
KLAG:
For a Klingon perhaps,

32:38.790 --> 32:43.043
but Riker's people do not volunteer
for death so easily.

32:44.420 --> 32:46.713
He may be a spy,

32:47.340 --> 32:49.967
but he's no coward.

32:50.134 --> 32:53.470
That only proves that he's intelligent,

32:53.680 --> 32:58.225
and you might not be as strong
as you used to be.

32:58.393 --> 32:59.434
[ALERT SOUNDS]

32:59.602 --> 33:01.979
KLlNGON OFFlCER:
Captain, l've picked up the Enterprise.

33:02.522 --> 33:03.981
So soon?

33:04.899 --> 33:07.818
The Enterprise
is on an intercept course with us.

33:07.986 --> 33:10.070
[DOOR OPENS]

33:11.406 --> 33:16.243
You almost had me believing
this was a misunderstanding.

33:17.537 --> 33:18.578
But?

33:18.788 --> 33:23.458
The Enterprise has changed course
and is following us. Why?

33:23.668 --> 33:24.751
Ask them.

33:24.961 --> 33:26.545
The reason is obvious.

33:26.754 --> 33:28.755
Their intent is clear.

33:28.965 --> 33:31.008
How long before we make contact?

33:31.175 --> 33:32.926
KLlNGON OFFlCER:
Less than 1 5 minutes, sir.

33:33.136 --> 33:34.803
Put the ship on full battle alert.

33:35.013 --> 33:36.805
Arm all photon torpedoes.

33:37.015 --> 33:41.143
Let them charge
into their destruction!

33:43.438 --> 33:45.856
Captain, our bearings show
that we should be in contact

33:46.024 --> 33:47.149
with the Klingon vessel now.

33:47.358 --> 33:50.110
- Slow to impulse.
WESLEY: Aye, sir. lmpulse speed.

33:50.319 --> 33:52.279
Hailing frequencies are open.

33:52.488 --> 33:53.947
There is no response.

33:54.157 --> 33:55.365
Continue transmission.

33:55.575 --> 33:58.535
The Pagh is either cloaked
or destroyed, sir.

34:01.039 --> 34:04.207
Conduct an intensive scan
of the area.

34:06.252 --> 34:08.587
The Enterprise has slowed
to impulse speed

34:08.796 --> 34:10.547
and is making an intensive sweep.

34:10.757 --> 34:12.466
Hold your position.

34:12.675 --> 34:14.509
Let them come to us.

34:14.719 --> 34:16.887
They may be here to help you.
Don't be a fool.

34:17.055 --> 34:18.263
[KARGAN GROWLS]

34:18.973 --> 34:22.309
Do not forget my rank.

34:22.518 --> 34:23.602
l haven't.

34:23.811 --> 34:26.438
l am simply trying
to help you understand.

34:26.647 --> 34:28.690
l understand fully.

34:28.900 --> 34:30.817
Now you understand.

34:31.027 --> 34:33.236
l am still captain of this vessel,

34:33.446 --> 34:36.114
and you are still crew
and sworn to obey me.

34:36.324 --> 34:38.992
- You gave me your oath.
- Yes, sir, l did.

34:39.202 --> 34:44.706
Then fulfill that oath
and serve this ship as you swore to.

34:45.208 --> 34:49.753
Tell me of the surest method
of attack against the Enterprise.

34:50.671 --> 34:52.964
- l won't.
- You must.

34:53.174 --> 34:56.051
lt is a matter of honor
and loyalty to your oath.

34:56.260 --> 35:00.055
l will not surrender the secrets
of the Enterprise to you.

35:00.223 --> 35:04.392
Arr, if your word is no good,
then how can we ever trust Starfleet?

35:04.602 --> 35:06.770
l will not break any vow
that l have taken in the past.

35:06.979 --> 35:08.939
l have also taken an oath
of loyalty to your ship.

35:09.148 --> 35:10.190
l will not break that.

35:10.399 --> 35:13.985
- They are in conflict!
- No, sir, they are not!

35:14.195 --> 35:15.320
l will obey your orders.

35:15.530 --> 35:17.489
l will serve this ship as first officer,

35:17.698 --> 35:19.741
and in an attack
against the Enterprise,

35:19.951 --> 35:22.160
l will die with this crew.

35:22.370 --> 35:27.207
But l will not break my oath
of loyalty to Starfleet.

35:28.918 --> 35:32.337
lf you had told those secrets
about the Enterprise,

35:32.547 --> 35:37.509
l would have labeled you a traitor
and killed you where you stood.

35:39.720 --> 35:42.806
But instead you will die with us.

35:43.599 --> 35:46.143
You will die like a Klingon.

35:49.355 --> 35:51.189
[BEEPlNG]

36:12.587 --> 36:15.255
Sir, l have something to report
to you immediately.

36:15.464 --> 36:16.506
Yes. Go ahead, ensign.

36:16.716 --> 36:19.551
l have managed to isolate
the organisms on our hull.

36:19.760 --> 36:21.344
They are a submicron form

36:21.554 --> 36:24.848
capable of breaking nuclear bonds
in the tritanium plating.

36:25.057 --> 36:26.975
But can they be removed
from the hull?

36:27.185 --> 36:28.935
Yes. They are controllable

36:29.145 --> 36:31.479
and can be removed
from the hulls of both ships

36:31.689 --> 36:34.107
by using a tunneling neutrino beam.

36:34.317 --> 36:35.859
Thank you, ensign. Well done.

36:36.360 --> 36:37.903
lnitiate that procedure.

36:38.112 --> 36:41.489
Lieutenant, add that information
to the hailing messages.

36:41.699 --> 36:43.533
Aye, sir.

36:44.827 --> 36:45.869
[ALERT SOUNDlNG]

36:46.037 --> 36:47.829
Lieutenant.

36:53.169 --> 36:55.503
The Enterprise
has changed hailing messages.

36:55.713 --> 36:58.089
They now include a promise
of cleaning the organisms

36:58.299 --> 36:59.549
and helping in repairs.

37:00.259 --> 37:02.719
l told you they're here to help.

37:03.221 --> 37:05.013
l do not believe them.

37:05.223 --> 37:09.100
Arm all weapons. Prepare to attack.

37:11.479 --> 37:15.440
PlCARD:
Captain's log, stardate 42507.8.

37:15.650 --> 37:17.692
Although our search
has been extensive,

37:17.902 --> 37:20.862
we are still unable
to locate the Klingon ship

37:21.072 --> 37:23.448
or any evidence of its destruction.

37:23.658 --> 37:25.617
DATA: Considering the absence
of debris, captain,

37:25.826 --> 37:26.952
it is reasonable to assume

37:27.161 --> 37:30.455
that the Klingon vessel
is in the area and cloaked.

37:32.041 --> 37:33.124
Agreed.

37:33.334 --> 37:37.337
And since we do not know its intent,
l recommend we go to red alert.

37:37.546 --> 37:39.339
- Make it so, lieutenant.
WORF: Aye, sir.

37:39.507 --> 37:40.548
[ALARM SOUNDS]

37:42.343 --> 37:44.719
The Enterprise
has raised its shields.

37:44.929 --> 37:47.681
That's normal procedure when
entering into a suspicious situation.

37:47.890 --> 37:51.685
lt's not an act of aggression.
The Enterprise will not fire first.

37:51.894 --> 37:54.729
Then they are fools...

37:55.439 --> 37:57.065
...for we will.

37:57.608 --> 37:59.359
You'll get only one shot.

37:59.735 --> 38:01.069
We'll only need one.

38:01.279 --> 38:03.530
Stand by on phasers and torpedoes.

38:03.739 --> 38:07.158
Prepare to fire them simultaneously.

38:07.535 --> 38:11.579
l recommend you don't fire
until you're within 40,000 kilometers.

38:11.998 --> 38:13.123
Why?

38:13.332 --> 38:15.333
lt will cut down their response time.

38:15.543 --> 38:18.044
You are honoring your promise
to serve us?

38:18.796 --> 38:20.463
Would you do less?

38:20.673 --> 38:24.592
You will give the order to fire,
Commander Riker.

38:25.761 --> 38:28.388
Call out distances.

38:29.015 --> 38:31.224
Any questions, Mr. Riker?

38:31.434 --> 38:34.185
There's one thing l'd like to say.
l question your judgment.

38:34.854 --> 38:39.607
ln my opinion, your reason for forcing
this confrontation is not valid.

38:40.276 --> 38:42.152
Are you finished?

38:43.112 --> 38:44.154
Yes, sir.

38:44.363 --> 38:46.614
Commence with attack as ordered.

38:46.824 --> 38:50.452
KLAG: Fifty-five thousand kilometers
and closing.

38:52.330 --> 38:54.497
ls that a weapon, commander?

38:55.082 --> 38:56.249
No, sir.

38:58.586 --> 38:59.753
Give it to me.

39:05.718 --> 39:08.845
We are receiving an emergency signal
from a command transponder.

39:09.055 --> 39:11.848
Location 035, mark 31 3.

39:12.266 --> 39:14.601
Frequency and code designate it
as Commander Riker.

39:14.977 --> 39:17.312
Chief O'Brien, lock on
to that transponder signal.

39:17.855 --> 39:18.897
Yes, captain.

39:19.106 --> 39:21.691
We are not yet in safe range
for a transfer.

39:21.901 --> 39:23.651
And defensive shields
are still in place.

39:23.861 --> 39:25.487
We may have to stretch it.

39:25.863 --> 39:27.864
We have to know what's going on,
and Commander Riker

39:28.032 --> 39:30.408
is the only one who can tell us.
We'll beam him directly here

39:30.576 --> 39:31.701
onto the Bridge.

39:31.911 --> 39:33.328
- On my command.
- Yes, sir.

39:33.537 --> 39:35.330
l'll wait till 40,000.

39:36.040 --> 39:37.791
Forty-eight thousand.

39:39.001 --> 39:40.251
Forty-four thousand.

39:40.461 --> 39:42.337
Transporter Room, stand by.

39:42.546 --> 39:43.588
You control the shields.

39:43.798 --> 39:44.881
Ready, sir.

39:45.049 --> 39:46.341
Forty thousand.

39:46.717 --> 39:48.593
Forty thousand kilometers.

39:48.803 --> 39:53.181
Prepare to drop cloaking shields
and fire when ready.

39:53.641 --> 39:55.558
Steady.

39:55.768 --> 39:57.644
Transporter Room, energize.

40:05.152 --> 40:06.653
RlKER:
Hold it where you are, Klag.

40:07.029 --> 40:08.655
l have relieved Captain Kargan.

40:08.864 --> 40:11.533
He was acting
in an irrational manner.

40:15.621 --> 40:17.664
l'm your captain now.

40:23.587 --> 40:24.796
KARGAN:
Where am l?

40:25.714 --> 40:27.799
You're onboard
the starship Enterprise.

40:29.802 --> 40:32.512
Arr, Riker has no honor.

40:32.721 --> 40:35.557
He tricked me! Aah!

40:35.724 --> 40:37.142
[GRUNTS]

40:41.272 --> 40:42.856
He is only dazed, sir.

40:43.065 --> 40:45.024
Oh, that's fine.

40:45.484 --> 40:47.819
But where's Commander Riker?

40:48.529 --> 40:50.488
Cloaking shields off.

40:55.870 --> 40:57.454
Obey my orders.

40:57.663 --> 40:59.622
We will be destroyed.

40:59.832 --> 41:03.543
lf we are, it will be in battle
and l will die with you.

41:03.752 --> 41:08.465
So l repeat, cloaking shields off.

41:11.677 --> 41:13.511
[BEEPlNG]

41:18.058 --> 41:20.185
WORF:
lt is the Pagh, sir.

41:20.394 --> 41:22.937
lt has all armament locked on us
and ready to fire.

41:23.147 --> 41:25.064
Hold this position.
Hailing frequencies.

41:25.274 --> 41:26.858
Calling the Pagh,
this is the Enterprise.

41:27.067 --> 41:29.736
We are here to assist. Do not fire.

41:30.488 --> 41:32.614
They will not believe you.

41:32.781 --> 41:34.365
PlCARD [ON-SCREEN]:
Pagh, we are here to assist.

41:34.533 --> 41:35.867
Do you read me?

41:37.995 --> 41:40.497
Enterprise,
this is Captain William Riker

41:40.706 --> 41:42.957
of the Klingon vessel, Pagh.

41:43.167 --> 41:46.294
I order you to lower your shields
and surrender.

41:51.133 --> 41:53.051
Lower shields.

41:53.886 --> 41:55.803
Surrender as ordered.

41:56.972 --> 42:00.642
l demand to be beamed back
aboard my vessel!

42:01.352 --> 42:05.480
Transporter chief, prepare to beam
Captain Kargan back aboard the Pagh.

42:05.648 --> 42:06.981
O'BRlEN [OVER lNTERCOM]:
Aye, sir.

42:07.149 --> 42:08.858
Captain Riker,

42:09.401 --> 42:11.611
we can carry out your repairs
immediately.

42:12.404 --> 42:14.781
Thank you, Captain Picard.

42:28.087 --> 42:29.754
You should have killed me.

42:29.964 --> 42:31.256
l don't want your command.

42:31.632 --> 42:33.341
But you tricked me to get it.

42:33.551 --> 42:35.176
Either way, you can have it back.

42:37.304 --> 42:39.847
Then return to your station.

42:44.186 --> 42:45.311
[KARGAN GROWLS]

42:47.147 --> 42:48.940
[RlKER GRUNTS]

42:54.863 --> 42:57.407
Get him off my ship.

42:57.783 --> 42:59.659
Yes, captain.

43:01.245 --> 43:04.956
You understand the Klingons
better than l thought, commander.

43:05.165 --> 43:07.458
Thank you, my friend.

43:11.964 --> 43:13.381
[DOOR OPENS]

43:14.758 --> 43:39.157
[SlGHS]

43:41.952 --> 43:45.121
That might have been one of the
shortest assignments in history.

43:45.789 --> 43:46.956
Wrong, Number One.

43:47.166 --> 43:49.000
lt was almost the longest.

43:49.209 --> 43:50.293
Well done.

43:50.628 --> 43:53.046
Thank you.
Actually, l learned quite a bit.

43:53.839 --> 43:55.882
Apparently not when to duck.

43:56.091 --> 43:58.718
When not to duck
would be more accurate.

44:00.262 --> 44:01.721
Welcome aboard, Number One.

44:01.930 --> 44:05.058
Now, lieutenant,
conduct the commander to Sickbay.

44:05.267 --> 44:06.893
Aye, sir.

44:07.394 --> 44:08.436
Commander?

44:13.734 --> 44:15.735
Your little toy worked. Thanks.

44:15.944 --> 44:18.071
l'm glad it did.

44:18.864 --> 44:21.532
You come from a very brave
and unique people.

44:21.742 --> 44:23.743
l'm glad you're with us
on the Enterprise.

44:23.952 --> 44:26.663
Thank you, commander,

44:27.164 --> 44:28.915
and welcome home.
